 &lt;a class="anchor" href="#diffusion-and-resistivity">#&lt;/a>
&lt;/h1>
&lt;!-- Talkin' bout Chen chapter 5 -->
&lt;p>Diffusion is a migration of particles that results in neutralization of any density gradients. Collisional processes affect the rate of diffusion. For example, particle random walks due to collisions can destroy plasma confinement.&lt;/p></description></item></channel></rss>